text: Cherkassy () is a rural locality (a selo) in Cherkassky Selsoviet, Ufimsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 710 as of 2010. There are 15 streets. == Geography == It is located 35 km from Ufa. == References == Category:Rural localities in Ufimsky District
title: Cherkassy, Ufimsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan
